Installation of Firebase

Login in Firebase from follwing url and click on Sign in.

https://firebase.google.com/

Step 1  :   Click on "Add project"

 

Step 2: Set "Project name" & "Country".

 

Step 3: Click on "Add Firebase to android app".

 

Step 4: Add details "Android Package Name", App Nickname (Optional) click on "Register app".

 

Step 5: Download "Google-services json" file and add it in android studio in specific location as per snap below. after that click on "Next" button.

Step 6: add depedencies in project gradle file and app gradle file as per snap. click on sync now in android studio to sync gradle.

Now your firebase is configured, you can check app liev user just reinstall app and verify.
